WEBVTT

00:22.188 --> 00:23.928
Morgan:
It'll be dark soon.

00:24.107 --> 00:25.096
Man:
It's not much further.

00:25.275 --> 00:26.390
(horse nickers)

00:26.568 --> 00:28.650
We have people
who can patch her up.

00:32.574 --> 00:33.814
What are you doing?

00:33.992 --> 00:35.857
I'm marking
our way back.

00:55.472 --> 00:57.303
- On your left!
- I've got it.

00:57.474 --> 00:58.463
(horse neighs)

00:58.641 --> 01:00.472
(gunshots)

01:00.643 --> 01:02.224
(walkers growling)

01:07.901 --> 01:11.485
(grunting)

01:11.654 --> 01:14.270
(gunshots)

01:30.423 --> 01:34.007
(walkers growling)

01:34.177 --> 01:36.634
(gunshots)

01:38.014 --> 01:39.515
(grunting)

01:42.685 --> 01:44.676
(gunshots)

01:44.854 --> 01:48.187
(panting)

02:14.175 --> 02:16.131
(growls)

02:16.302 --> 02:19.385
(walkers growling)

02:22.809 --> 02:23.798
(horses neighing)

02:23.977 --> 02:26.844
- (grunts)
- (horse neighs)

02:29.149 --> 02:31.515
(horse neighs)

02:56.217 --> 03:00.927
(growls)

03:05.310 --> 03:07.722
(hoofbeats)

03:11.482 --> 03:12.813
Man: Whoa.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.895
Daniel. Colton.

03:15.069 --> 03:18.061
Good.

03:18.239 --> 03:20.480
We've been looking
for you.

03:20.658 --> 03:22.774
It looks like you found
some people yourself.

03:22.952 --> 03:24.237
(horse snorting)

03:59.989 --> 04:03.322
(birds chirping,
wind chimes clinking)

04:19.008 --> 04:22.341
(indistinct conversations
in distance)

04:41.322 --> 04:44.405
How long
have I been asleep?

04:44.575 --> 04:45.826
(sighs)

04:45.994 --> 04:49.031
Two days,
more or less.

04:58.089 --> 05:00.296
Where are we?

05:00.466 --> 05:02.206
Doctor says
you're healing up,

05:02.385 --> 05:04.216
said it could have been
much worse,

05:04.387 --> 05:06.378
but you had
some luck.

05:06.556 --> 05:09.218
And your pack
with the weapons--

05:09.392 --> 05:11.553
they wanted
to lock them up.

05:11.728 --> 05:15.016
Seeing as they were helping us,
I didn't argue.

05:15.189 --> 05:18.397
It'll be with them
until we're ready to leave.

05:18.568 --> 05:21.025
I figure
that'll be another week,

05:21.195 --> 05:23.060
maybe a little more,

05:23.239 --> 05:25.821
andthen
we can start back to Alexandria.

05:27.618 --> 05:30.234
- What is this place?
- Well, the people here,

05:30.413 --> 05:34.998
they, um-- they call this place
"The Kingdom."

05:40.423 --> 05:43.915
(indistinct conversations)

05:44.093 --> 05:46.300
(bird chirping)

05:46.471 --> 05:48.928
They were helping you...

05:49.098 --> 05:50.258
so I've been
helping them.

05:50.433 --> 05:51.513
(man speaking indistinctly)

05:51.684 --> 05:53.845
Hey.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.601
Yeah.

05:58.107 --> 06:00.564
Did you-- did you tell them
about what happened to me,

06:00.735 --> 06:01.770
about who we are?

06:01.944 --> 06:04.526
Why?
Who are we, Carol?

06:04.697 --> 06:06.233
What did
you tell them?

06:08.034 --> 06:10.821
and they saw
what I did to him.

06:10.995 --> 06:12.405
We got split up.

06:12.580 --> 06:13.911
You found trouble.
I found you.

06:14.082 --> 06:15.447
That is
all he knows.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.240
All who knows?

06:17.418 --> 06:18.624
The man
I'm taking you to see,

06:18.795 --> 06:21.002
the person who's in charge
of this place.

06:21.172 --> 06:23.458
This person
have a name?

06:23.633 --> 06:26.420
(animal bleating)

06:26.594 --> 06:29.131
- Morgan?
- Yeah.

06:29.305 --> 06:30.590
He, um--

06:33.142 --> 06:35.007
he's called
"King Ezekiel."

06:35.186 --> 06:36.301
What?

06:36.479 --> 06:37.514
Yeah.

06:37.688 --> 06:39.144
King Ezekiel.

06:39.315 --> 06:40.680
(chuckles)

06:43.152 --> 06:44.608
And, um...

06:46.614 --> 06:47.603
he does
his own thing.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.272
See?

06:51.953 --> 06:55.161
Uh, what does
that mean?

06:55.331 --> 06:56.446
Well...

06:56.624 --> 06:59.991
(breathes sharply)
...here we are.

07:00.169 --> 07:02.285
(tiger growling)

07:07.969 --> 07:09.175
Yeah.

07:09.345 --> 07:13.258
I, uh,
I forgot to say that...

07:14.517 --> 07:16.257
Ezekiel has a tiger.

07:17.603 --> 07:20.720
(roars)

07:22.150 --> 07:26.359
(music playing)

08:02.231 --> 08:05.564
(tiger growling)

08:05.735 --> 08:08.226
Ezekiel:
Shiva, enough.

08:08.404 --> 08:11.066
The fair maiden has been through
a myriad of trials.

08:11.240 --> 08:14.698
- (growling continues)
- They are our guests.

08:14.869 --> 08:16.234
Chill it up,
IIS-II

08:16.412 --> 08:17.913
Chill it up!

08:20.082 --> 08:23.245
Jerry,
you are a faithful steward,

08:23.419 --> 08:26.582
but your words
leave me pitch-kettled.

08:26.756 --> 08:29.247
I understand
your concern, Shiva.

08:29.425 --> 08:30.926
You haven't met Carol.

08:31.093 --> 08:32.674
Nor have I.

08:32.845 --> 08:34.801
But if she is a friend
of Morgan,

08:34.972 --> 08:37.224
we shall consider her
a friend of the realm

08:37.391 --> 08:39.768
until proven otherwise.

08:39.936 --> 08:41.221
She's doing better,

08:41.395 --> 08:43.772
thanks to you
and your people, so...

08:43.940 --> 08:45.180
Indeed.

08:45.358 --> 08:48.646
It pleases me to see you
up and about, Carol.

08:48.819 --> 08:50.901
I am King Ezekiel.

08:51.072 --> 08:53.609
Welcome to the Kingdom.

08:53.783 --> 08:56.445
(Shiva snorts, growling softly)

09:07.296 --> 09:11.084
You have been addressed
by the king, yet you remain silent.

09:12.301 --> 09:15.418
Do I detect skepticism?

09:15.596 --> 09:18.133
Perhaps you think me mad.

09:18.307 --> 09:20.923
Perhaps you see this place
as nothing more than a mirage.

09:21.102 --> 09:24.936
So... tell me...

09:25.106 --> 09:27.848
what do you think
of The Kingdom, Carol?

09:28.859 --> 09:31.601
What do you think
of the king?

09:37.702 --> 09:41.115
I... think
you're amazing.

09:41.289 --> 09:42.995
It's amazing.

09:43.165 --> 09:45.326
And your Sheba--

09:45.501 --> 09:47.787
It's, uh, "Shiva."

09:47.962 --> 09:50.874
Shiva.

09:51.048 --> 09:52.037
Amazing.

09:52.216 --> 09:55.834
I would be speechless
if I wasn't already speaking.

09:56.012 --> 09:58.128
I don't know
what the hell's going on

09:58.306 --> 09:59.671
in the most wonderful way.

09:59.849 --> 10:01.510
(both chuckle)

10:01.684 --> 10:05.472
As Morgan is aware, I encourage
those who find respite here

10:05.646 --> 10:07.352
to enjoy
the fruits of our grandeur

10:07.523 --> 10:12.142
for as long as they like,
so long as they contribute.

10:12.320 --> 10:15.107
Drink from the well,
replenish the well...

10:15.281 --> 10:17.112
once you've healed,
of course.

10:17.283 --> 10:18.318
Of course.

10:18.492 --> 10:20.528
Of course.
All about the well.

10:20.703 --> 10:22.910
Well-said.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.492
Jerry...

10:25.666 --> 10:27.372
Ah, where are
my manners?

10:27.543 --> 10:29.784
(snaps fingers)

10:29.962 --> 10:30.951
Please, partake.

10:31.130 --> 10:35.669
We have magnificent apples,
nectarines, pomegranates--

10:35.843 --> 10:38.255
all grown right here
inside the kingdom.

10:38.429 --> 10:41.421
It's fruit time.

10:41.599 --> 10:43.885
I-I couldn't.

10:44.060 --> 10:46.972
Oh, come, now.
At least take a pomegranate.

10:47.146 --> 10:50.229
You know, I always found them
too much trouble.

10:50.399 --> 10:52.515
Sweet fruit
surrounded by bitter--

10:52.693 --> 10:54.024
they're something
of a contradiction,

10:54.195 --> 10:56.686
but heaven for the effort.

10:56.864 --> 10:59.071
You park some chocolate in front
of me and watch it go bye-bye,

10:59.241 --> 11:02.278
but pomegranates,
just not for me, thanks.

11:02.453 --> 11:05.195
Well, if there's anything
you want or need--

11:05.373 --> 11:07.614
if you enjoy music,

11:07.792 --> 11:10.909
we have a guitarist whose talent
brings tears to the eye,

11:11.087 --> 11:12.247
and we have
a small choir.

11:12.421 --> 11:13.581
Thank you.

11:13.756 --> 11:16.589
All I need
is some more rest...

11:16.759 --> 11:17.919
and maybe
a hairbrush.

11:18.094 --> 11:19.254
(chuckles)

11:19.428 --> 11:21.885
No one told me
I'd be meeting royalty.

11:24.225 --> 11:25.465
Anyway...

11:25.643 --> 11:27.975
uh, Your Majesty--

11:28.145 --> 11:30.431
I should call you
"Your Majesty," right?

11:30.606 --> 11:31.891
You can.

11:32.066 --> 11:34.899
Thank you,
Your Majesty.

11:35.069 --> 11:36.775
It's a pleasure.

11:36.946 --> 11:39.062
The pleasure is mine, Carol.

11:39.240 --> 11:40.776
Be well.

11:45.413 --> 11:46.573
(Shiva growls)

11:53.963 --> 11:55.203
- Hey.
- Hi.

11:57.258 --> 11:58.623
Look, I know.

11:58.801 --> 12:00.166
You're shitting me,
right?

12:00.344 --> 12:01.629
Now, it's--
it's a lot.

12:01.804 --> 12:03.089
He is, um...

12:03.264 --> 12:05.095
I don't know.
lt-- it--

12:05.266 --> 12:06.722
Stop it.
Stop this.

12:06.892 --> 12:08.803
This place
is a damn circus,

12:08.978 --> 12:10.309
all of it.

12:10.479 --> 12:12.470
Th-these people,
this is make-believe.

12:12.648 --> 12:14.058
It's playtime.

12:14.233 --> 12:16.064
And you're just...

12:16.235 --> 12:17.520
(laughs)

12:17.695 --> 12:19.060
I can't do this.
I can't be here.

12:19.238 --> 12:20.273
Look, Carol,
these people found--

12:20.448 --> 12:22.655
No, I can't, Morgan.
I won't.

12:22.825 --> 12:24.611
I'll wait.

12:24.785 --> 12:26.286
And when you're not there
to stop me,

12:26.454 --> 12:28.536
when nobody else is,
I'll go.

12:28.706 --> 12:29.821
You know
I can't let you.

12:29.999 --> 12:31.330
No. |'||--

12:31.500 --> 12:33.161
You'll what?

12:33.335 --> 12:34.711
Tie me up
like that wolf?

12:34.879 --> 12:36.289
Is that it?

12:37.882 --> 12:41.090
It isn't
up to you.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.670
It wasn't before
in the basement,

12:42.845 --> 12:45.211
it wasn't at the library,
and it isn't now.

12:45.389 --> 12:46.890
I don't give a shit

12:47.057 --> 12:48.513
if you think
you've found the secret to life.

12:48.684 --> 12:49.799
- |--
- No, I don't. I don't.

12:49.977 --> 12:52.093
I don't, and I haven't.
And I know what I've started.

12:58.944 --> 13:01.651
But I won't let you die
out there.

13:02.698 --> 13:04.279
That's what
I won't do.

13:09.371 --> 13:11.498
It doesn't matter
what you do.

13:20.591 --> 13:23.708
(engine starts)

13:29.809 --> 13:31.925
(gate thuds)

13:37.066 --> 13:40.433
(snorting, growling)

13:40.611 --> 13:41.942
Morgan:
Where we going?

13:42.112 --> 13:43.898
- Ezekiel: Hunting.
- Hunting what?

13:44.073 --> 13:46.655
What was once captive
to the farm

13:46.826 --> 13:48.942
now runs free
in the city.

13:49.119 --> 13:50.245
(snorting)
Here!

13:50.412 --> 13:51.663
- Come on!
- Man: Come on!

13:51.831 --> 13:52.991
- Come on!
- Come on! Whoo!

13:53.165 --> 13:54.405
- Come on!
- Come on!

13:54.583 --> 13:56.414
- Turn! Turn!
- Whoo, whoo! Come on!

13:56.585 --> 13:57.916
- Hunting!
- Go now! Go now!

13:58.087 --> 13:59.167
- Go!
- Come on!

13:59.338 --> 14:00.327
- Go now! Go now!
- Come on!

14:00.506 --> 14:01.495
(walker growling)

14:01.674 --> 14:03.835
Go now! Go now! Go!
Come on!

14:04.009 --> 14:06.591
_( _ - Go!
pig squeals)

14:06.762 --> 14:08.343
Well-done,
Richard.

14:08.514 --> 14:11.972
It's just
what we needed.

14:12.142 --> 14:14.633
(growling continues)

14:14.812 --> 14:17.975
Why the Walker?

14:19.775 --> 14:21.811
We're herding them in.
Why do you need bait?

14:21.986 --> 14:24.978
Because I want their bellies
full of rot.

14:25.155 --> 14:28.147
That's why.

14:28.325 --> 14:31.658
(pigs squealing)

14:34.206 --> 14:37.118
You shoot a machine gun
in the woods, and nothing.

14:37.293 --> 14:38.999
You cough in the city, and...

14:39.169 --> 14:40.420
(walkers growling)

14:41.755 --> 14:43.666
Ezekiel:
Diane, retrieve the truck.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.456
We'll take our leave.

14:45.634 --> 14:47.886
(growling continues)

14:53.392 --> 14:54.757
Ben...

14:54.935 --> 14:57.642
you're up.

14:57.813 --> 14:59.519
Use the machete.

14:59.690 --> 15:03.308
Just as you and he
have practiced.

15:03.485 --> 15:06.227
Yeah.
Like we practiced.

15:06.405 --> 15:08.191
(breathes deeply)

15:08.365 --> 15:09.525
(grunting)

15:09.700 --> 15:11.611
(growling)

15:18.584 --> 15:21.826
(sighs)

15:25.883 --> 15:27.794
(growling stops)

15:31.430 --> 15:33.170
Do not be troubled,
Benjamin.

15:33.349 --> 15:34.885
Next time.

15:39.271 --> 15:41.512
No one back home
needs to know about this.

15:41.690 --> 15:43.191
Morgan:
You mean the pigs--

15:43.359 --> 15:45.270
that they're eating
the dead?

15:46.862 --> 15:48.523
Any of it.

15:48.697 --> 15:51.985
(truck engine running)

15:55.120 --> 15:57.372
(walker growling)

15:57.539 --> 15:58.574
- (grunts)
- (walker thuds)

15:58.749 --> 16:00.489
(walkers growling)

16:05.798 --> 16:08.039
May we one day cease you all
from this curse!

16:08.217 --> 16:10.424
Till then, know that
we live on in your place...

16:10.594 --> 16:14.052
- (truck door closes)
- ...full, festive, faithful, and free.

16:14.223 --> 16:16.384
Only halfway free.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.677
(truck doors closing)

16:36.745 --> 16:38.827
Where are they going?

16:38.998 --> 16:40.738
Somewhere else.

16:54.471 --> 16:56.553
(gate creaks)

17:00.269 --> 17:04.763
(gate creaks, thuds)

17:10.946 --> 17:12.811
Your skill
with the staff...

17:15.367 --> 17:17.779
...how did you come to acquire
that skill?

17:18.954 --> 17:22.162
It was a cheesemaker,
a friend.

17:23.375 --> 17:25.036
(chuckles)

17:25.210 --> 17:28.623
I imagine your comrade would be
very proud of you this day.

17:28.797 --> 17:29.832
(chuckles)

17:30.007 --> 17:32.373
For saving Ben
in a single blow.

17:35.971 --> 17:37.472
There's a saying--

17:37.639 --> 17:41.052
the pessimist looks down
and hits his head.

17:41.226 --> 17:43.057
The optimist looks up...

17:43.228 --> 17:45.389
andloses
his footing.

17:46.398 --> 17:48.354
The realist
looks forward

17:48.525 --> 17:51.187
and adjusts his path
accordingly.

17:53.197 --> 17:56.610
I believe young Benjamin's path
is in need of adjustment.

17:58.994 --> 18:02.157
Would you train him,
as your friend trained you?

18:02.331 --> 18:03.662
I don't...

18:03.832 --> 18:04.992
I don't know
that I'm the--

18:05.167 --> 18:06.247
Benjamin
has shown aptitude

18:06.418 --> 18:08.704
with neither blades
nor munitions.

18:08.879 --> 18:11.666
Perhaps his failings lie
in the weapons...

18:11.840 --> 18:14.172
perhaps
it's the teacher...

18:15.260 --> 18:16.511
and perhaps it's both.

18:16.678 --> 18:18.179
Hey, look,
you know...

18:18.347 --> 18:21.680
the man I shot
to save Carol--

18:21.850 --> 18:23.761
