22:17.461 --> 22:18.541
(grunts)

22:18.712 --> 22:21.579
Hey,
what's the book?

22:21.757 --> 22:25.295
It's, uh--
It's philosophy.

22:25.469 --> 22:28.927
- You know, we should really get back--
- You mind if! borrow it?

22:29.097 --> 22:32.510
I've just read
every book in this place...

22:32.684 --> 22:34.265
twice...

22:34.436 --> 22:36.768
including an air-conditioning
repair textbook.

22:36.938 --> 22:38.098
- (chuckles)
- (chuckles)

22:38.273 --> 22:40.104
Just so you know,
the number-one problem

22:40.275 --> 22:43.312
with an HVAC system
isn't refrigerant leaks.

22:43.487 --> 22:44.772
Yeah.

22:44.946 --> 22:46.322
Won't spoil that one
for you.

22:46.490 --> 22:47.900
(chuckles)

22:48.950 --> 22:50.531
Please?

22:53.705 --> 22:55.491
Here.

22:57.501 --> 22:58.786
(chuckles)

22:58.960 --> 23:01.337
Ezekiel: Gentlemen...

23:01.505 --> 23:04.042
come with us,
both of you.

23:04.216 --> 23:07.800
We have matters of import
to attend to.

23:07.969 --> 23:10.460
Bring your gun,
Morgan.

23:14.643 --> 23:16.053
(wind rushing)

23:18.230 --> 23:19.686
Ezekiel: The swine
are slaughtered

23:19.856 --> 23:22.233
far from
The Kingdom...

23:22.401 --> 23:26.144
lest their screams carry in
the wind and invite questions.

23:26.321 --> 23:31.236
What we are doing here is
a secret I keep from my people.

23:31.410 --> 23:35.153
Some see secrets
as a privilege of ruling.

23:35.330 --> 23:39.994
They are burdens,
not part of the reward.

23:40.168 --> 23:41.328
They are the cost.

23:41.503 --> 23:43.539
(brakes squeal, engine rumbling)

23:47.843 --> 23:51.006
(engine shuts off)

23:51.179 --> 23:54.512
(vehicle doors closing)

24:03.191 --> 24:05.898
Gavin: Here, Iwas worried
we were early.

24:06.069 --> 24:07.525
Our arrangement

24:07.696 --> 24:10.438
is something I consider
with the utmost seriousness.

24:13.994 --> 24:18.408
Yes, indeedy, you do,
and you will.

24:20.125 --> 24:22.958
(music playing)

24:23.128 --> 24:25.870
(sighs)
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7.

24:26.047 --> 24:29.881
I count 8--
that's good.

24:30.051 --> 24:32.042
They look bigger than last time.
That's good, too.

24:32.220 --> 24:33.426
They were well-fed.

24:33.597 --> 24:35.178
I made sure of it.

24:35.348 --> 24:37.760
We appreciate
your hospitality.

24:37.934 --> 24:40.892
Lucky for us,
we brought two trucks.

24:41.062 --> 24:45.226
How about you, uh,
help us load 'em up?

24:48.612 --> 24:50.102
They're part
of another group.

24:50.280 --> 24:52.692
- They call themselves--
- I know who they are.

25:03.168 --> 25:05.250
(pig thuds, truck gate closes)

25:07.839 --> 25:12.253
Hey, asshole,
how about a smile?

25:12.427 --> 25:15.919
This--
this is nothing.

25:16.097 --> 25:18.088
We've been
letting you off easy.

25:22.646 --> 25:25.604
You sure you don't
have that backwards, kid?

25:25.774 --> 25:28.106
(chuckles)

25:28.276 --> 25:29.686
Yeah.

25:29.861 --> 25:31.943
I'm sure.

25:32.113 --> 25:33.853
(grunts)

25:36.451 --> 25:37.816
(grunting)

25:37.994 --> 25:39.109
(guns cock)

25:39.287 --> 25:41.448
Ezekiel:
Cease this.

25:41.623 --> 25:43.159
(both grunting)

25:48.630 --> 25:50.621
(blows landing)

25:50.799 --> 25:53.882
Lower your weapons.

25:55.387 --> 25:56.877
Richard...

25:57.055 --> 25:58.295
let him go.

26:01.893 --> 26:03.133
(coughs)

26:03.311 --> 26:06.724
This is not what we do.

26:08.775 --> 26:10.515
Free shots?

26:10.694 --> 26:12.230
Oh, I love
this shit.

26:13.572 --> 26:15.153
(grunts)

26:15.323 --> 26:18.315
Gavin,
tell your man to stop.

26:18.493 --> 26:20.449
- (grunts)
- Gavin!

26:20.620 --> 26:24.363
Jared! Jared!
The man said stop!

26:25.500 --> 26:26.831
And he's been good to us.

26:27.002 --> 26:29.288
We've taken up
more than enough of his time.

26:31.423 --> 26:35.917
(whistles)

26:45.270 --> 26:48.558
Richard,
we will discuss this.

26:48.732 --> 26:50.848
Come on.

26:51.026 --> 26:52.516
(breathing heavily)

26:52.694 --> 26:54.025
Gavin: Same time next week,
Ezekiel, all right?

26:54.195 --> 26:58.188
It's produce week,
so... produce.

26:58.366 --> 27:00.618
You got the list--
not one bit less.

27:02.203 --> 27:03.329
(vehicle door closes)

27:03.496 --> 27:07.284
Otherwise... you know...

27:07.459 --> 27:08.869
he's gonna
have to go first.

27:09.044 --> 27:11.581
(engine starts)

27:14.132 --> 27:17.374
(imitating pig squealing)

27:21.097 --> 27:24.385
You've encountered them
before?

27:24.559 --> 27:25.799
Their group?

27:25.977 --> 27:27.217
Yeah.

27:29.230 --> 27:30.436
The man you killed
to save Carol--

27:30.607 --> 27:33.269
he was one of them,
as well?

27:33.443 --> 27:36.560
He was, yeah.

27:36.738 --> 27:39.229
(sighs)

27:39.407 --> 27:41.864
Is that
why you wanted me here?

27:43.578 --> 27:45.660
Because I could do it again
if I had to?

27:45.830 --> 27:47.912
No, Morgan.

27:48.083 --> 27:50.620
Quite the opposite,
in fact.

28:06.476 --> 28:08.262
(indistinct conversations)

28:09.938 --> 28:11.803
Benjamin: Whoa.
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey.

28:11.981 --> 28:13.937
Where you going,
hmm?

28:14.109 --> 28:15.770
It's movie night tonight.

28:15.944 --> 28:17.104
I want to get a good seat.

28:17.278 --> 28:19.985
Right, but you were gonna
clean your plate, though, first.

28:20.156 --> 28:21.191
(sighs)

28:21.366 --> 28:24.574
Come on.
That was the deal, Dutch.

28:24.744 --> 28:27.451
- Yeah.
- (crunching)

28:27.622 --> 28:29.078
Wow.
Good one, smart guy.

28:29.249 --> 28:31.615
All right, well,
just be in bed by 10:00,

28:31.793 --> 28:33.033
not a minute later.

28:33.211 --> 28:34.291
But I can read?

28:34.462 --> 28:35.872
Yes,
you can read.

28:36.047 --> 28:37.332
All right.

28:37.507 --> 28:40.123
(conversations continue)

28:40.301 --> 28:41.882
(both chuckle)

28:42.053 --> 28:43.884
He's a good kid.

28:44.055 --> 28:46.296
Yeah.
Yeah, he is.

28:47.809 --> 28:48.798
(door closes)

28:48.977 --> 28:50.808
I only kind of know
what I'm doing raising him.

28:50.979 --> 28:54.563
Ezekiel's been
a big help.

28:55.650 --> 28:56.981
You seem close...

28:57.152 --> 28:59.393
you and the king.

28:59.571 --> 29:02.153
Yeah, he was, uh,
pretty tight with my dad.

29:03.700 --> 29:06.362
My father
was a good fighter.

29:06.536 --> 29:09.369
One of the best
in The Kingdom.

29:09.539 --> 29:11.655
How'd it happen?

29:15.086 --> 29:17.042
It was about a year ago.

29:18.339 --> 29:21.547
Ezekiel sent his detachment out
to clear out a building.

29:22.886 --> 29:25.673
There was too many wasted
and not enough backup.

29:28.683 --> 29:31.174
Eight men
didn't make it out.

29:31.352 --> 29:33.729
My father
was one of 'em.

29:35.899 --> 29:40.518
But E-Ezekiel--
he's a lot more careful now.

29:40.695 --> 29:44.688
He told me that it,
uh, well...

29:46.201 --> 29:49.864
He, uh, told me he was keeping
his deal with that group quiet

29:50.038 --> 29:52.120
'cause he thinks
the people would want to fight.

29:54.125 --> 29:57.288
He says that even if we did,
we wouldn't win--

29:57.462 --> 30:00.078
at least,
not without losing people...

30:00.256 --> 30:01.917
maybe a lot of 'em.

30:02.091 --> 30:03.797
And you think
he's right...

30:05.428 --> 30:06.964
that we
shouldn't fight?

30:07.138 --> 30:08.378
I don't know.

30:08.556 --> 30:09.762
I mean...

30:09.933 --> 30:11.548
I don't know
if I know enough to know.

30:11.726 --> 30:12.932
(chuckles)

30:14.604 --> 30:16.720
Maybe you do.

30:18.066 --> 30:19.556
Hey, um...

30:19.734 --> 30:22.897
there was an inscription
in the book.

30:23.071 --> 30:26.484
It was handwritten--
about not killing.

30:26.658 --> 30:28.944
- Is it yours?
- It's not, no.

30:29.118 --> 30:30.779
'Cause I also noticed

30:30.954 --> 30:33.821
you only put vegetables
on your plate during dinner.

30:33.998 --> 30:36.375
And, I mean,
you're teaching me aikido,

30:36.543 --> 30:38.124
and if aikido
means not to kill,

30:38.294 --> 30:39.283
then that means
that you're--

30:39.462 --> 30:40.918
It's not about
what I think.

30:41.089 --> 30:42.420
People can--

30:42.590 --> 30:45.673
they can try and set you
in the right direction,

30:45.844 --> 30:48.961
but they can't
show you the way.

30:49.138 --> 30:53.802
You know, you got to find that
for yourself, and...

30:53.977 --> 30:56.434
I thought I had it.

30:56.604 --> 30:57.935
Idid.

30:59.774 --> 31:03.483
But I'm-- I'm just
fumbling through.

31:07.615 --> 31:09.822
Sometimes,
we change our minds.

31:14.831 --> 31:17.197
Well, hey, do you want
to catch movie night?

31:17.375 --> 31:18.455
I can't.

31:18.626 --> 31:20.457
I, uh...

31:20.628 --> 31:23.210
I got to
talk to Carol.

31:23.381 --> 31:24.996
But thank you.

31:26.301 --> 31:31.170
(clinking)

32:12.972 --> 32:14.963
(insects chirping)

32:19.687 --> 32:22.349
(animal howls in distance)

32:25.693 --> 32:27.354
Ezekiel:
By all means, fair maiden.

32:27.528 --> 32:28.779
Have one.

32:34.369 --> 32:35.950
This enclosure
was built

32:36.120 --> 32:38.907
for the purpose
of common recreation and study.

32:39.082 --> 32:43.542
I had it repurposed into
a garden worthy of our splendor.

32:43.711 --> 32:47.545
I dare say it's my favorite
place in the entire Kingdom.

32:49.342 --> 32:52.254
It pleases me that you've
seen it with your own eyes

32:52.428 --> 32:55.795
before choosing
to leave us so suddenly.

32:55.974 --> 32:57.885
Geez, yeah, I...

33:00.228 --> 33:01.388
I'm real sorry
about this.

33:01.562 --> 33:03.644
Um,
it's just...

33:03.815 --> 33:06.557
What good am I here?

33:08.152 --> 33:12.145
Jerry...
would you excuse us?

33:12.323 --> 33:13.483
(inhales deeply)

33:13.658 --> 33:15.569
If you need me,
holler.

33:15.743 --> 33:17.734
lkeep
in hollering range.

33:22.250 --> 33:26.584
Ezekiel: Ifl hadn't
happened upon you right now--

33:28.131 --> 33:30.338
what's that saying?

33:35.930 --> 33:39.673
Never bullshit
a bullshitter.

33:39.851 --> 33:41.842
Have I got that right?

33:42.020 --> 33:45.763
The sweet-and-innocent act
you've been doing--

33:45.940 --> 33:47.555
it's quite clever.

33:48.651 --> 33:51.188
Worked on me.

33:51.362 --> 33:53.774
Blend in,
get people to trust you,

33:53.948 --> 33:55.449
acquire what you need
from them,

33:55.616 --> 34:00.201
and then you're gone,
as if you were never there.

34:00.371 --> 34:03.704
The guns you brought here
in your pack--

34:03.875 --> 34:05.957
they belong
to Saviors.

34:06.127 --> 34:09.039
What do you know
about the Saviors?

34:09.213 --> 34:12.125
More than I care to,
unfortunately.

34:12.300 --> 34:14.757
They nearly
extinguished you.

34:14.927 --> 34:19.011
But you did more than put up
a fight, Carol-- you won.

34:20.975 --> 34:22.385
(chuckles)

34:22.560 --> 34:24.972
By ending up here?

34:26.981 --> 34:29.063
That's funny
to you?

34:29.233 --> 34:31.485
(sighs)

34:31.652 --> 34:35.236
You're a joke.
This place is.

34:38.326 --> 34:41.363
Out there--
Out there, it's real.

34:41.537 --> 34:44.495
I've been to places where
I thought I wouldn't have to--

34:44.665 --> 34:46.075
where I could just be.

34:48.169 --> 34:50.160
You're selling these people
a fairy tale.

34:50.338 --> 34:51.999
Maybe they need
the fairy tale.

34:52.173 --> 34:55.040
Maybe the contradiction
is the point.

34:55.218 --> 34:56.628
And ruling over people

34:56.803 --> 34:59.761
and having your ass kissed
by everyone's just a perk?

35:08.106 --> 35:09.846
May I?

35:26.541 --> 35:28.873
People want
someone to follow.

35:31.712 --> 35:33.373
It's human nature.

35:33.548 --> 35:37.382
They want someone
to make 'em feel safe.

35:37.552 --> 35:41.090
And people who feel safe
are less dangerous...

35:41.264 --> 35:43.550
more productive.

35:43.724 --> 35:49.094
They see a dude
with a tiger, shoot,

35:49.272 --> 35:53.891
they start tellin' stories
about finding it in the wild,

35:54.068 --> 35:58.437
wrestling it into submission,
turning it into his pet.

35:58.614 --> 36:01.651
They make the guy
larger than life,

36:01.826 --> 36:03.316
a hero.

36:03.494 --> 36:06.281
And who am I
to burst their bubble?

36:06.455 --> 36:10.698
Next thing you know,
they treat me like royalty.

36:13.296 --> 36:14.411
They wanted--

36:14.589 --> 36:19.709
they needed someone to follow,
s-so |-- I acted the part.

36:22.305 --> 36:24.591
| faked it
till I made it.

36:29.478 --> 36:31.730
I was a zookeeper.

36:35.526 --> 36:37.141
Shiva, she fell into

36:37.320 --> 36:40.278
one of the concrete moats
in her exhibit.

36:40.448 --> 36:43.315
It was empty,
the vets were on their way,

36:43.492 --> 36:45.619
but her leg
was ripped open.

36:45.786 --> 36:47.526
She was gonna bleed out.

36:49.790 --> 36:52.827
The sound she made.

36:54.837 --> 36:56.793
She was in
so much pain.

36:59.342 --> 37:01.628
I knew the risk.

37:01.802 --> 37:04.544
I had to try.

37:04.722 --> 37:08.306
And I got my shirt up
around her leg...

37:09.477 --> 37:11.388
saved her life.

37:13.981 --> 37:15.312
After that,
she never showed

37:15.483 --> 37:17.769
so much as a tooth
in my direction.

37:21.572 --> 37:24.564
Keeping a tiger
isn't practical, I know.

37:24.742 --> 37:27.108
She eats
as much as 10 people.

37:27.286 --> 37:29.402
She could yank the chain
out of my hand--

37:29.580 --> 37:31.821
hell, she could
yank my arm right off.

37:33.376 --> 37:36.834
But she hasn't.

37:37.004 --> 37:38.915
She won't.

37:41.842 --> 37:44.504
I lost a lot,
just like everybody else.

37:46.764 --> 37:50.131
When it all started to end,
I found myself back at the zoo.

37:51.394 --> 37:56.013
Shiva was
one of the last animals left.

37:56.190 --> 37:59.102
She was trapped...

38:00.111 --> 38:01.601
hungry, alone.

38:04.865 --> 38:07.197
Like me.

38:07.368 --> 38:10.451
She was the last thing left
in this world that I loved.

38:13.207 --> 38:15.243
She protected me.

38:15.418 --> 38:20.378
She got me here,
made me larger than life.

38:20.548 --> 38:22.379
And I made
this place.

38:25.303 --> 38:28.045
I used to act
in community theater,

38:29.557 --> 38:31.889
played a few kings
in my day...

38:32.059 --> 38:33.390
(chuckles)

38:33.561 --> 38:35.893
Arthur, Macbeth...

38:36.063 --> 38:37.803
Martin Luther.

38:37.982 --> 38:39.392
(chuckles)

38:39.567 --> 38:42.604
My name really is Ezekiel,
though.

38:43.904 --> 38:45.064
(sighs)

38:45.239 --> 38:47.446
That's 100% real.

38:53.456 --> 38:55.788
Cards on the table.

38:55.958 --> 38:58.449
Nothing up my sleeve.

38:58.627 --> 39:02.085
I'd appreciate you
keep this between us, though,

39:02.256 --> 39:03.871
for them.

39:05.926 --> 39:08.133
And, yeah,
a little bit for me.

39:13.100 --> 39:15.591
(sniffles)
I don't care.

39:16.937 --> 39:19.519
You do
what you want.

39:19.690 --> 39:22.306
Ijust want
to go.

39:22.485 --> 39:24.271
Go where?

39:26.697 --> 39:28.483
Carol.

39:30.951 --> 39:32.361
Away.

39:36.582 --> 39:37.947
I'm sorry.

39:38.125 --> 39:40.537
For what?

39:42.713 --> 39:46.171
For whatever bad
you've been through.

39:46.342 --> 39:48.708
There's so much of it
out there now, you know?

39:50.721 --> 39:52.131
(sighs)

39:54.141 --> 39:55.927
Too much.

39:57.978 --> 40:01.391
Out there,
it feels like it's all bad,

40:01.565 --> 40:04.352
especially when
you're alone.

40:04.527 --> 40:05.892
(sighs)

40:06.070 --> 40:08.732
The thing is,
though...

40:10.533 --> 40:12.740
it's not all bad.

40:14.328 --> 40:16.740
It can't be.
It isn't.

40:18.541 --> 40:20.327
Life isn't.

40:20.501 --> 40:21.832
Where there's life,

40:22.002 --> 40:27.713
there's hope, heroism,
grace, and love.

40:30.094 --> 40:32.176
Where there's life,
there's life.

40:32.346 --> 40:35.258
I hope that's not
what you're walking away from.

40:37.810 --> 40:39.596
So what if I am?

40:39.770 --> 40:41.556
Maybe you don't
have to.

40:41.730 --> 40:43.595
I made
my own world here.

40:43.774 --> 40:45.184
I found a way
to deal with the bad

40:45.359 --> 40:47.190
by going a little overboard
with all the good.

40:47.361 --> 40:48.601
Ijust...

40:49.947 --> 40:52.029
embraced
the contradiction.

40:53.701 --> 40:56.283
Maybe you could, too,
in your own way.

40:56.454 --> 41:00.697
Like, maybe you could go
and... not go.

41:00.875 --> 41:03.457
Yeah, I-I sound like
a crazy person.

41:03.627 --> 41:04.707
I get it.

41:04.879 --> 41:06.619
You know,
maybe I am.

41:06.797 --> 41:10.210
But I think
I can help...

41:10.384 --> 41:12.340
if you let me.

41:14.346 --> 41:16.598
Why do you care?

41:18.976 --> 41:22.594
'Cause it makes me
feel good.

41:24.190 --> 41:26.181
I'll get your stuff together,

41:26.358 --> 41:27.643
find somebody I trust
to meet you at the gate,

41:27.818 --> 41:30.730
so you can go
and-- and not go.

41:30.905 --> 41:33.738
We'll see
if I'm on to something

41:33.908 --> 41:36.820
or if it's just
more bullshit.

41:38.996 --> 41:41.032
What do you say?

42:00.184 --> 42:03.472
You're sure this is
what you want, right?

42:03.646 --> 42:05.056
lam.

42:07.274 --> 42:09.060
It's up to you.

42:10.653 --> 42:13.065
It should have always
been up to you.

42:17.993 --> 42:20.609
Whoa.

42:20.788 --> 42:23.495
Whoa.

42:34.009 --> 42:35.294
Okay?

42:35.469 --> 42:38.302
(horse whinnies)

42:38.472 --> 42:40.713
(snorts)

42:40.891 --> 42:43.132
Got it.

42:45.312 --> 42:46.688
(sighs)
Stay there.

42:46.855 --> 42:48.311
It's good we're here.

42:49.692 --> 42:51.398
- (snorts)
- How's that?

42:51.569 --> 42:53.309
10 more minutes,
and I might start to regret

42:53.487 --> 42:56.695
all the times
I tried to shoot and stab you.

43:01.203 --> 43:04.115
I think you're my favorite
person I ever knocked out.

43:05.249 --> 43:07.535
Definitely
top two or three.

43:07.710 --> 43:09.325
(chuckles)

43:12.715 --> 43:15.172
Take care
of yourself.

43:15.342 --> 43:17.924
I will.
Do you promise?

43:18.095 --> 43:21.508
Always watching,
always ready, remember?

43:21.682 --> 43:24.845
I do.

43:26.437 --> 43:28.519
Okay.

43:49.209 --> 43:50.915
Thank you.

43:56.550 --> 43:59.166
(lock clanking)

44:00.763 --> 44:02.048
Whoa.

44:02.222 --> 44:05.055
(gate creaking)

44:05.225 --> 44:09.093
(sighs)

44:09.271 --> 44:11.432
(gate closes)

44:28.499 --> 44:29.989
(walker growls)

44:30.167 --> 44:32.453
(growling)

44:41.595 --> 44:43.631
(growling stops, walker thuds)

44:56.443 --> 44:58.479
(knock on door)

45:05.619 --> 45:09.157
(Shiva growls)

45:16.004 --> 45:19.667
